        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v477uZXqBtxW_yXSybnj7r9DYJ3C4X0_Gx2782XBZ1tQdUwcb36KNLMFPkHjVQYTZ46mmi-jALimFToLqW9sFGLDePmzFEBeWPITek5LXGmpK7CBcKA" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>The Norman Church was once a cathedral and built in Norman times. There was once an adjacent Anglo-Saxon cathedral to St Mary before the Norman building too. Both Michael and Mary intercept here at a central node point. The church is also named The Holy Cross ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436-labelson</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v477uZXqBtxW_yXSybnj7r9DYJ3C4X0_Gx2782XBZ1tQdUwcb36KNLMFPkHjVQYTZ46mmi-jALimFToLqW9sFGLDePmzFEBeWPITek5LXGmpK7CBcKA</value>
