      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Creech St Michael</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v50S5721VkpGvIr1xaFHW0iUbR4WGYKYQuiIjEtipaFPYfSO2R-BBLVS5m1xSnjU4jC2fCSRvcwQt7doBYP5yuuCH8Tvj68CPcMfD-G_e165EOwz03YCSaD8bI" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Church of St Michael. The present building - according to the church guide - 'was built on a site of pagan worship'. Michael and Mary currents converge, and narrow down to a point, then cross in the centre of the main isle like a celtic cross]]></description>
