      <Placemark>
        <name>Burrowbridge Mump</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6ehtCJnh0Hxponpi6-WUDFnePYjYoAAEDY29SBo7BRlAzub7AMTB8GiYNwYqBYKjRv_kOxvj4RcFdPczwdB6kvkW3bHOdEdmpLHg6eHYz433Xn4yUI" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Burrow Mump is also known as St Michael's Borough or Tutteyate. The church on top of the Mump was probably first built in Saxon times, dedicated to St Michael. On a clear day the Tor can be seen from the Mump - though the Mump cannot be seen from the Tor.]]></description>
