      <Placemark>
        <name>Ivinghoe Beacon</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7rFwWUn7lysFHjVsArLbQymbBOPAHy_aY92XL05chjys4bMj160hcJGu5n1IFbAjPvm-HOIywRcZ8KPncI9ECqD14K7cVEfzz4PfGPFkzZF-Q67JUVMs4Z11B8" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Lying on the Icknield way the 'hill fort' that crowns the beacon was a centre for Saxons and Celts, a focus for fire rituals that punctuated their annual cycle.<br><br><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4QNh9a9bPpsph1SzrBFhfJBSVvn8ApffAbhmDxahvgi-OQ9AjkVXjc0UsH8ZjgEUR_tVcdNNy2pWSuZFFj1kSCr7C4anzOYUpgkKiCqCwPJHsrjfAKdueAkA" height="200" width="auto" />]]></description>
