      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Waulud's Bank, Luton]]></name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7sKzA_ggLt0XvkwXZ9BsoIWsctwxjDHT20caf4r-j1e6YY-cxAfEksdMhXhDnLfmKGZ-MJVR6Y6nHWpGfbkMjeNuaslSQu-Y-sEomb6Q6fK_IE2CYvjnpOvGn0tQ" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Waulud's Bank, is located at Five Springs, also the name of some 14 storey tower blocks and surrounded by the conurbation of Luton. Five Springs is the source of the Rive Lea and the earthwork has been dated to be contemporary with Avebury. The Luton Carnival, which has traditionally been held on the Whitsun May bank holiday, is the largest one-day carnival in Europe]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436-labelson</styleUrl>
