      <Placemark>
        <name>Eye</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7rO_uR5AgD28hfyLlJWdaz3I-_Vzzh414ahlSDHG35_x01GpmGHfENfKflMUgPHFc4fL6-Yf48xMb_MFObmb4sL-ez0BoYIlsH8CUoM6GJnsrLdKg" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Aerial photographs show that this steep mound looks like an eye when viewed from above.It would have been an sacred island in the flooded flats surrounding the town. the church is huge and very grand for a small place. the mound has had castles, a windmill, a victorian folly as well as evidence of bronze age  activity. ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436-labelson</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7rO_uR5AgD28hfyLlJWdaz3I-_Vzzh414ahlSDHG35_x01GpmGHfENfKflMUgPHFc4fL6-Yf48xMb_MFObmb4sL-ez0BoYIlsH8CUoM6GJnsrLdKg</value>
