      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Sinoden Hill, Wittenham Clumps</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4suqdscVv2QWpdy4v4AGW-PiBxdI4Y6uT-9JEVVrJmDYJgjM1NXgLWTifjhkG0mrSGlRKGgfY33OW5xKiXkyfyY25O5ZyjTjyMxo3ZJVrXu5tKpwvsAN740j0Mf7Zf8S8HxRD1nA" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Dorchester was the site of the first Baptism of an Anglo Saxon King. St Birinus created a Saxon Cathedral here and in 635AD he baptised the Saxon King Cyneglis in the river Thame. Sinoden Hill and Wittenham Clump is part of a pre Christian sacred landscape like the Avebury complex. A henge bigger than Stonehenge used to exist in the now flooded gravel beds next to the river. ]]></description>
