            -4.6386914,50.4214867,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[St Michael's Mount]]></name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5os0rfuKgc7koVp7RXhEn_3bSxqBh3qCBMavGYCpFsCKstpgfjwl-_y3nCyDqnM-gzOimKMiL_qXM2j_P2pJAY1GTaQQF-6to9ZYcg2uVd3WtFevLrStG4wGZ5E48" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>The first association of St Michael with the island was in 465AD. A group of fishermen experienced an incandescent vision in which the archangel appeared starting a tradition of Christian pilgrimage to the shrine. Previous ages had also looked on the the Mount as a special place.The Christian imagery of St Michael replaced earlier gods of light and creation and points to a tradition of sun worship and a divinity connected with solar energies. ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436-labelson</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5os0rfuKgc7koVp7RXhEn_3bSxqBh3qCBMavGYCpFsCKstpgfjwl-_y3nCyDqnM-gzOimKMiL_qXM2j_P2pJAY1GTaQQF-6to9ZYcg2uVd3WtFevLrStG4wGZ5E48</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -5.5025196,50.1281307,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>The Holy Cross, Crediton</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5F7tPIciqu56tLk2L7Bxo-eiFhgkXIfdS2-FpIY275u2-kSy_mwrKMPKE3VqOZDvKDAqb7WTZXRiuxv45P47k3sk6p47o38Robru5VIQpOYCt6QMWZWYUNUwfZCxmyi3vU" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>The Holy Cross where the two currents cross in the centre of the cruciform in plan building. Important place and with holy wells and an old Mary chapel nearby. With its Norman tower it was originally a cathedral. Dedicated to St Boniface of Anglo Saxon Parentage he visited Rome and travelled Europe as a missionary creating monasteries.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436-labelson</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
