        <name>Holy Well, Doulting</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5O_JvGvcIh8yJkE0I_lhcFuWwMjnMn4W5x1PYO-KJuQj5pJ-lpjy9Rc43x0RwUHDciSYLBeV-nL60SUuUt0EpgzuSdNXyr8RZ-kmLngqKe4Ezmr96d1pRg_Oe1dQ" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>The well is hidden down a no through road beneath the church on the hill above. A very romantic place and although hidden, the spring has many visitors, many leave offerings on the tree branches of coloured cloth ribbons, even notes and personal memoaibilia.]]></description>
