      <Placemark>
        <name>Leedstown</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6f8i0a9aRbf_e1lweaVAy8qKCtl6u7m_j4bkH4DLd_4K_0ZTjGW-yEBZHQVNBDDr3cDmK48lpDx_1P4S76bXa9DpMnkWpOVDwYleoxfQwC2adN" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This Victorian chapel was built only 150 years ago on virgin ground. Built by Edward White Benson, Bishop of Truro. Broadhurst speculates that this chapel was built here as it is on the St Michael line and the the he knew about its location in relation to St Michael Mount. Benson became Archbishop of Canterbury]]></description>
