      <Placemark>
        <name>Mells</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4AReEv3GZiBWbK50c4MXOlRBA4-G6D4oLwbsS_WwUdpvRlVocK8vG-i9Hg5qRuwzIKvmtedQ_anUA91iKJTuKTTGNJsIDLKqrEivWJ57ZD6BTHnK6Nln8LebGb_kE_izFSiv9ZLdo" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Mells is a very Grand church heavily restored in Victorian times The axis of the church coincides exactly with the Michael current. There is a well on the north side reminiscent of Chalis Well in Glastonbury. ]]></description>
