      <Placemark>
        <name>Menacuddle Sacred Spring</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5Snt-AlMHefH1cX0HzonghydR7nQxNe4Rudm3GY9jfhy1L4SL5fvQEt1ei6xWnxOOsv8WHy-jh1HsVFnpUIVPp0MCG3esG4rmEqNv85FjeQluqIbF_gT0i2X7OIpUQ0jvHx0qX" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Gothic style Holy well built in to the rock face below the main road. The place is long revered for its mystical virtues hidden by the river in its enchanted glade. There is a strange other worldy atmosphere here. The stone carved druids chair is legendary for 'dreaming'. The place was also frequented by monks of old and seems to have a protective ambience.]]></description>
