      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[St Michael's Chapel, Roche Rock]]></name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5Bw2oLUTTe8XeckHItp7RHbV5sYoW5sBNVQNHMEvz39j8usov2TRb4rxuR01HsHMpP09OznSWQf9y6x5hsv-XFmNI5zqQzkVt9wCOzdQlYpvlKWSWIUQ" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Set in a landscape moulded in to hills and valleys of heavy industry and mining Roche rock is startling. Pylons and china clay spoil mountains. The rock itself is a fine example of quartz shorl; a fully tourmalinised granite, with black tourmaline crystals. On its summit, built in to the rock is and ancient chapel dedicated to St Michael. Legend tells of an early Celtic saint. St Conan, who took refuge at this hermitage to commune with God. He became on of the first Bishops of Cornwall. eventually he left the rock for St Michael's Mount. <br><br><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7P3FAwytWAVCkTWHGENyimpa1Uoc0zKeeyTweAnERJhuFWl-ABCrgptUWwm4JYVtxRuOoadiJBq9ORY0kt3Ch-AtJpUKa9J2hnZd2pVwNDJOc4eKoKd8s7CEytYSjKVx7oZwJym-I" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6__xTsCLf2_Aw15xSbErijLTxwYLB1mEIy62StI8ywS-uueZ4Xxmr3-z5a2-sS_v2ApdpJ3IB7T0SQ5voToyi5QhAW5Sqe-e8-6VfG0xeD9WZ5dUY" height="200" width="auto" />]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436-labelson</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
