      <Placemark>
        <name>St Germoe</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v621qFGosNRVLYKmmnExNxedfUSyamyaHhKnpQY3XQT7jw53qH8o78sohl8aVi1kAL9p56hGYrNNtckqDwbyDTy4-tAMK1z4li1n-tCNC3A_nrW9A" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Set next to a stream. St Germoe's chair set to rear. The church and village are named after St Germoe, one of the celtic saints who arrived from Ireland with his sister Brecca in the 5th century.<br><br><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6z5uwh0Ba-_OOgLeQa0j1iJYjC8g_RhwyPZQKS3kDPunK7NX5OgEH6yRSS0D9puw53KIe7JACHtxt2cieCBgowtZKnodXdzs__Z4V81b8QhNwuSwEzLFqx2_c" height="200" width="auto" />]]></description>
