        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4b5ZCpCnLrnNJdlSGp-GTYQ5s-tgS1pw5GJivBBSjvS8QGtNyF9bGXD31t0okh-d3P8TEc4o3gRGTz3Cq-y2CsyCW38MIeWJinzQ7nU191qxfWUeRZ59tg8ydGChtr5G4" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Striking, long, thin 12th century building with octagonal belfry on top of a round tower. It has a thatched roof and is in the middle of no where. Very strong reaction to the Mary current felt here.<br><br><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6qz1yNoGp3S1lhMdMFsN5iMAGQJtsz6y1xnXCt_hc8N4MRd8rB_X9uleq51zgRWQ8T04horLMDZ8nRI0qVO1pQvJtuuVd8H2ZvMjZv3H1JxF-hjN1hx-8r" height="200" width="auto" />]]></description>
